title: Snap Reports Slowest-Ever Quarterly Growth but Adds New Users
description: The maker of Snapchat has been struggling with a sharp slowdown in its advertising business.

title: Are We Past Peak Newsletter?
description: The humble email newsletter, which became a star in its own right, appears headed back to earth.

title: How Disinformation Splintered and Became More Intractable
description: Ahead of the midterm elections, the proliferation of alternative social media sites has helped cement false and misleading information as a defining feature of American politics.

title: Texas Sues Google for Collecting Biometric Data Without Consent
description: Ken Paxton, the state attorney general, said products like Google Photos and the Nest camera had violated Texans’ privacy rights.

title: U.S. Details How It Plans to Police Foreign Firms
description: A government committee issued new guidelines for how it determines penalties for foreign companies that break agreements to protect U.S. national security.
